Letter Presented to Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 18 (KCNA) -- A letter was presented to leader Kim Jong Il by Reggie Ranatunge, director-general of the Asian Regional Institute of the Juche Idea, and Harish Gupta, secretary general of the institute, on April 8 on behalf of the participants in the Asian regional seminar on the Juche idea.
 The seminar provided its participants with an opportunity to clearly realize that the global peace, prosperity and happiness of humankind can be achieved and guaranteed only when sincere efforts are made for economic development, social justice and democracy, the letter said, adding that they were unanimous in understanding that the Juche idea and the Songun politics indicate a true way of attaining the above-said great goals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Juche idea and the Songun politics serve as a key to helping the people win social justice, something they could not enjoy worldwide and also show the way for individuals to make progress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Juche idea is a man-centered philosophy instilling the inviolable dignity and pride into the people and providing them with an equal status. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also helps them conduct independent, creative and conscious activities to exercise their dignity and rights, aware of their duty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Juche idea and the Songun politics help the people of all social standings unite as an integral whole. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Juche philosophy regards independence as a common idea.
 The letter said they are convinced that Korea would be surely reunified in the near future under the dynamic and wise leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Asian Regional Seminar on Juche Idea Held in India 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 18 (KCNA) -- An Asian regional seminar on the Juche idea was held in India on April 8.
 It was attended by Director General of the International Institute of the Juche Idea Vishwanath, Honorary President of the World Peace Council Romesh Chandra, Director General of the Asian Regional Institute of the Juche Idea Reggie Ranatunge, and delegations from Sri Lanka, Bangladesh, Nepal, Pakistan, Mongolia and Japan, and leading officials and members of Juche idea study groups and people from different walks of life in India. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present there was a delegation of the Korean Social Scientists Society.
 Congratulatory speeches were made at the seminar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers highly praised President Kim Il Sung for his undying feats performed for the cause of global independence and leader Kim Jong Il for his Songun leadership exploits. They stressed that it is only the Juche idea that indicates the way of ensuring genuine independent development and wellbeing of the popular masses, economic progress, social justice and democracy under the present complicated situation.
 A keynote report and speeches were made at the seminar. The reporter and speakers said that the immortal Juche idea provides the popular masses with genuine democracy.
 Underscoring the need for the Asian nations to develop their independent national economies, opposed to the imperialists' moves for "globalization," obstacles to their independent progress, they called for boosting cooperation among Asian countries for democracy, economic development and social justice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The seminar adopted a declaration, which said the DPRK has not fallen victim to the U.S. sinister plots as it has followed the Songun policy set out by Kim Jong Il.
 Asian countries should unite close to frustrate the wicked design of the imperialist forces, the declaration said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Juche idea study organizations under the Asian Regional Institute of the Juche Idea declare that they will deepen the study of the Juche idea and the Songun politics and apply them to actual conditions of their countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Reiterating our will to more fervently follow the Juche philosophy and the Songun politics, we extend solidarity to the Korean people and express belief that Korea will surely be reunified in the near future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the seminar.

Foreign Figures Issue Statements on Day of Sun 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 18 (KCNA) -- Wahid Al Uksouri, chairman of the Misr Arab Socialist Party of Egypt, and Andy Brooks, general secretary of the Central Committee of the New Communist Party of Britain, released statements respectively on April 10 and 11 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 The former recalled that President Kim Il Sung had extended support, material and moral, to the Egyptian people in their struggle to restore the lost territory and said the Party and the government of the DPRK were standing behind the Arab people as ever in their cause of justice to regain the legitimate rights. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the Arab people are greatly inspired by the struggle of the Korean people against the arbitrariness of the United States and for defense of the sovereignty of the country and national dignity, he said, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the Songun policy of leader Kim Jong Il, the DPRK is advancing unswervingly along the road chosen by it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Andy Brooks in his statement said President Kim Il Sung was a great revolutionary who devoted his all to the prosperity of the country and happiness of the people.
 Noting that the cause of Kim Il Sung is being successfully carried forward to accomplishment by Kim Jong Il, he expressed the conviction that the Korean people rallied close around Kim Jong Il would achieve great successes in the struggle for the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and national reunification.

Joint Friendly Gathering of Delegations of Juche Idea Study Groups
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 18 (KCNA) -- Members of delegations of the Juche idea study groups from different countries had a joint friendly gathering on Monday. 
 It was attended by the visiting delegations and delegate of Juche idea study organizations in different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were members of the Korean Social Scientists Society, including Vice-Chairman Rim Hoe Song. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants noted that the immortal Juche idea, fathered by President Kim Il Sung, has been developed and enriched by leader Kim Jong Il. And they expressed their will to intensify the study and dissemination of the Juche idea, with the honor of being its followers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They sang "Nostalgia", a celebrated masterpiece, and other songs in praise of the great men and enjoyed multifarious sports and amusement games, deepening friendship.

Cambodian King Feted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 18 (KCNA) -- The Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly hosted a reception at the People's Palace of Culture on April 17 in honor of Cambodian King Norodom Sihamoni on an official visit to the DPRK.
 Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the SPA, in a speech at the reception said that the DPRK visit of the Cambodian king is an expression of the firm will of the king and the people of Cambodia to value and steadily develop the traditional relations of friendship and cooperation between the two countries and greatly encourages the Korean people in their vigorous drive to step up the building of a great prosperous powerful nation and the cause of independent national reunification.
 The Korean people will make positive efforts for the development of traditional relations of friendship with the Cambodian people and extend support to the Cambodian people in their efforts to achieve the peace and stability of the country and the unity of the nation, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Highly praising the king for devotedly striving for the prosperity of the country and the well-being of the people, true to the intention of the great king, he sincerely wished the king greater success in his future work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Cambodian king in a speech expressed his wholehearted admiration at the fact that leader Kim Jong Il who is carrying forward the cause of President Kim Il Sung has built great Korea into a country most developed in all fields and provided an excellent basis for the reunification of the country as required by the Juche idea.
 The king expressed his full support to the righteous line set forth by Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, supreme leader of the Korean people, to peacefully reunify the country.
 The continued mutual visits of the high-ranking leaders of the two countries century after century have further strengthened the bilateral ties of great friendship and unity and cooperation in various fields in the common interests of the two peoples, he said, adding that the cooperative relations between the two countries will make an affirmative contribution to the stability and development of the region and the world.
 Present on invitation were suite members of the king, Cambodian Ambassador to the DPRK Chhorn Hay and embassy officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the Cabinet, Kim Jin Song, minister of Culture, Kim Yong Il, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, Choe Han Chun, DPRK ambassador to Cambodia, Kim Jae Gon, vice-chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A performance was given by the artistes of the Mansudae Art Troupe at the reception.

Russian Artistes Perform for Guests of Honor
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 18 (KCNA) -- A performance was given for guests of honor by the art troupe of the Moscow Tchaikovsky State Conservatory and the Moscow State Academy Symphony Orchestra of Russia in the 24th April Spring Friendship Art Festival at the Ponghwa Art Theatre on Monday. 
 Appreciating the performance were Kim Yong Nam, Pak Pong Ju, Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop, Kim Ki Nam and Kim Jung Rin, officials of the party and power organs, public organizations, ministries and national institutions, educational, cultural and media institutions and working people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Andrei Karlov and the staff members of the embassy were among the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The art troupe of the Moscow Tchaikovsky State Conservatory put on the stage a glee of an immortal masterpiece "Nostalgia". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Russian artistes successfully presented with unique and rich voice and perfect ensemble a solo and a chorus of the Korean songs "May the Motherland Prosper" and "Blue Sky over My Country". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The audience was struck with deep impression when they presented choruses "My Motherland" and "Rye Field," a glee "Glory" from the opera "Ivan Susanin" composed by Glinka and the first and fourth movements of a string orchestra "Serenade" composed by Mozart and other numbers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The artistes of the Moscow State Academy Symphony Orchestra presented with refined rendition the Korean song "Arirang" loved by the Koreans with an orchestra, delighting the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The symphony orchestra impressively staged the fourth movement "Glory to the General" from the symphony suite "Long Journey for Songun Leadership," winning the acclaim of the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also staged orchestra "Bokaliz" composed by Rakhmaninov, "Polonez" from the opera "Eugene Onegin" composed by Tchaikovsky, "Interlude No. 5" from ballet "Raimond" composed by Glazunov, deeply impressing the audience.

Successful Stands of Flower Festival
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 18 (KCNA) -- Many flower stands, which have been arranged with rich content and in unique forms, are catching the eyes of the visitors to the on-going 8th Kimilsungia Festival.
 In particular, the crowd always gathers before the stand of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland, which is displayed on the first floor of the festival venue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The square-shaped stand resembles to a horizontal model board. Taking the rear part of the stand is the picturesque Mangyongdae in April where various kinds of flowers are in full bloom. Seen there are Mangyong Hill where President Kim Il Sung trained his body and mind in his childhood and a stream of people visiting the native home surrounded with flowers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the central part of the stand, a Korean map is depicted with immortal Kimilsungias. And standing both sides of its map are a model of the autographic monument inscribed with the letters "Kim Il Sung 1994. 7.7." written by the President in a document related to national reunification and a model of the Monument to the Three Charters for National Reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the front part of the stand there is a rainbow bearing the letters "Reunification 6.15" flanked by two sculptures showing two women pouring the water of Mt. Paektu and Mt. Hanna into one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The stand resembles to a large art work decorated in harmony with Kimilsungias and various kinds of flowers and plants. It makes the people recollect the immortal feats the President performed in the efforts for accomplishing the reunification cause.
 Conspicuous are the stands of the Ministry of Public Health, the Ministry of Light Industry and the Kyonghung Guidance Bureau. 
 The Ministry of Public Health adorns its stand with an anion water generator containing clear water of the Lake Chon on Mt. Paektu and is bringing the immortal flowers into full bloom. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The stands of 25 organizations of overseas Koreans and 79 foreign organizations including the diplomatic missions and non-governmental organizations in the DPRK reflect well the reverence of the world progressive people for the President, a peerless great man. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kathrin Rebecca Turner, an actress of the famous art troupe of Australia, went round the flower festival while attending the 24th April Spring Friendship Art Festival. Charmed by the flower festival, she said that at the flower exhibition, she came to know more clearly the greatness of President Kim Il Sung and he would live long in the minds of the Korean people.
